# LOOM Workspace: my-feature

This workspace was created by [LOOM](https://github.com/subotic/loom) and contains linked worktrees for multi-repo development.

## Repositories

| Directory | Branch | Source |
|-----------|--------|--------|
| `dsp-api` | `loom/my-feature` | git@github.com:dasch-swiss/dsp-api.git |
| `dsp-das` | `loom/my-feature` | git@github.com:dasch-swiss/dsp-das.git |

## Working in this workspace

- Each subdirectory is a git worktree checked out on the workspace branch.
- Changes in one repo's worktree do not affect the original repo until pushed.
- Each repo may have its own `CLAUDE.md` with repo-specific context.
- Use `loom exec <cmd>` to run a command across all repos.
- Use `loom save` to push all branches.
- Use `loom status` to see per-repo branch and dirty state.

## Sandbox

This workspace runs with sandbox enabled. Always try to work within the
sandbox constraints first — use paths that are within the workspace, prefer
tools and commands that don't require outside access, and structure your
approach to stay within allowed boundaries.

Only if a command genuinely cannot work within the sandbox (e.g., accessing
system binaries, global config, or paths in other worktrees), use
`dangerouslyDisableSandbox: true` on the Bash tool call. The user will
still be prompted to approve each such command.
